WorldStage Newsonlineâ€“ SFS Capital Nigeria Limited, a leading Nigerian non-bank financial institution has assets under management and advisory in excess of N100 billion has announced a distribution of N7.30 per N100 ordinary share to subscribers to its SFS Real Estate Investment Trust (SFS REIT), subject to approval will be paid to unitholders whose names appear in the register of its members as at the close of business on Friday, September 04, 2020. In a note filed by Tolg Nominees, Company Secretary at the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE), the Register of unitholders will be closed from Monday, September 07, 2020 to Friday, September 11, 2020. The qualification date for payment of distribution was put at Friday, September 04, 2020 while on Friday, September 25, 2020, distribution will be paid electronically to unitholders whose names appear on the Register of Members as at Friday, September 04, 2020, and who have completed the e-dividend registration and mandated the Registrar to pay their distributions directly into their Bank accounts.